SIMPLE: waxen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waxen
<hw>Wax"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of
wax.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The female bee, that . . . builds her <xex>waxen</xex>
cells.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Covered with wax; waxed; <as>as, a <ex>waxen</ex>
tablet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling wax; waxy; hence, soft;
yielding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men have marble, women <qex>waxen</qex>, minds.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Waxen chatterer</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
Bohemian chatterer.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waxiness</ent>⟦br⟧
